desc: Overnight: A 30 percent chance of showers, mainly before 5am.  Areas of fog.  Otherwise, cloudy, with a low around 58. Calm wind.
Sunday: A 20 percent chance of showers before 11am.  Areas of fog before 11am.  Otherwise, mostly cloudy, with a high near 67. Calm wind becoming southeast 5 to 7 mph in the afternoon.

Sunday Night: Showers likely after 2am.  Areas of fog after 2am.  Otherwise, mostly cloudy, with a low around 56. East wind around 10 mph.  Chance of precipitation is 70%. New precipitation amounts of less than a tenth of an inch possible.

Monday: Showers likely, mainly before 2pm.  Areas of fog before 8am.  Otherwise, cloudy, then gradually becoming mostly sunny, with a high near 66. East wind 9 to 13 mph becoming southwest in the afternoon.  Chance of precipitation is 60%. New precipitation amounts between a tenth and quarter of an inch possible.
Monday Night: Partly cloudy, with a low around 49. West wind 9 to 11 mph, with gusts as high as 21 mph.
Tuesday: Mostly sunny, with a high near 57.
Tuesday Night: Partly cloudy, with a low around 45.
Wednesday: Sunny, with a high near 59.
Wednesday Night: Mostly clear, with a low around 46.
